hands_on_practices.solution:
The fixed point $\mathbf{x}^*$ satisfies
$$
(I - A)\mathbf{x}^* = \mathbf{b}\,.
$$
Here 
$$
I - A = \begin{pmatrix}
1-a & -c & 0 \\
-c & 1-a & 0 \\
0 & 0 & 1-d
\end{pmatrix}
=\begin{pmatrix}
\frac{3}{4} & -\frac{1}{8} & 0 \\
-\frac{1}{8} & \frac{3}{4} & 0 \\
0 & 0 & \frac{2}{3}
\end{pmatrix}.
$$

The $2\times2$ block has determinant
$$
\det = \left(\frac{3}{4}\right)^2 - \left(-\frac{1}{8}\right)^2
=\frac{9}{16}-\frac{1}{64}
=\frac{35}{64}\,,
$$
so its inverse is
$$
\begin{pmatrix}
\frac{3}{4} & -\frac{1}{8} \\
-\frac{1}{8} & \frac{3}{4}
\end{pmatrix}^{-1}
=\frac{64}{35}
\begin{pmatrix}
\frac{3}{4} & \frac{1}{8} \\
\frac{1}{8} & \frac{3}{4}
\end{pmatrix}.
$$

Thus for $\mathbf{b}_{12}=(\frac{1}{4},\frac{1}{4})^T$ we get
$$
\begin{pmatrix}x^*\\y^*\end{pmatrix}
=\frac{64}{35}
\begin{pmatrix}
\frac{3}{4}&\frac{1}{8} \\
\frac{1}{8}&\frac{3}{4}
\end{pmatrix}
\begin{pmatrix}\frac{1}{4} \\ \frac{1}{4}\end{pmatrix}
=\frac{64}{35}\begin{pmatrix}\frac{7}{32} \\ \frac{7}{32}\end{pmatrix}
=\begin{pmatrix}\frac{14}{35} \\ \frac{14}{35}\end{pmatrix}
=\begin{pmatrix}\frac{2}{5} \\ \frac{2}{5}\end{pmatrix}.
$$

For the $z$-component,
$$
z^*=\frac{b_3}{1-d}
=\frac{\frac{1}{4}}{\frac{2}{3}}
=\frac{3}{8}.
$$

Hence the sum is
$$
S = x^* + y^* + z^* = \frac{2}{5} + \frac{2}{5} + \frac{3}{8} = \frac{4}{5} + \frac{3}{8} = \frac{47}{40}.
$$
